                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5229: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 27, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3259. For <persName corresp="#p_PFL">Polk</persName>.</p>
                <p>Department’s 3198, September 22. We have been advised that Treasury has funds
                    available provided plan for withdrawal of Czecho-Slovak troops is approved.
                    Early decision urgent or it will be too late to move the men before winter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
